+## 8. Proof & Case Study Collection Standards
+
+### Why This Section Exists
+The biggest trust gap in v2 is not tone — it is **proof readiness**. If the site launches before a deep case-study library exists, it needs a disciplined interim proof strategy.
+
+### Interim Proof Stack (Before Case Studies Are Live)
+Use, in order:
+1. clear positioning
+2. founder credibility
+3. real screenshots of work
+4. clear process
+5. communication standards
+6. early testimonials once approved
+
+Do **not** compensate for missing proof with louder copy.
+
+### Case Study Intake Checklist
+For every future project, capture:
+- client business type
+- city / market
+- services delivered
+- starting problem
+- launch or optimization date
+- baseline metrics
+- post-change metrics
+- source of truth for each metric
+- screenshots before and after
+- client quote approval status
+- permission to publish name / logo / screenshots
+
+### Publication Rules
+- No case study goes live without client permission
+- No claim goes live without a source
+- No “results” section without a timeframe
+- No giant percentages without raw-number context when scale is tiny
+- If multiple business changes happened at once, note that
+- If seasonality likely influenced results, note that
+
+### Minimum Threshold to Publish `/case-studies`
+Recommended threshold:
+- **at least 2 approved case studies with real metrics**, or
+- **1 strong metric-backed case study + 2 approved testimonials + real screenshot proof**
+
+Until that threshold is met, the site should rely on interim proof blocks instead of a public proof hub.
 
